WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:02.573
IT IS SO COLD!

00:02.573 --> 00:03.674
MY FINGERS SHRANK, AND NOW
MY RING WON'T STAY ON.

00:05.076 --> 00:07.007
DID YOU FIND OUT
WHY THE HEAT'S NOT WORKING?

00:07.007 --> 00:08.739
YES. YES, I DID.

00:08.739 --> 00:10.141
DO YOU REMEMBER
THREE MONTHS AGO

00:10.141 --> 00:11.642
WHEN WE SPLIT UP
OUR HOUSEHOLD DUTIES

00:11.642 --> 00:13.484
AND YOU WANTED TO BE IN CHARGE
OF PAYING THE BILLS?

00:13.484 --> 00:15.216
I HAVE AN AWESOME SYSTEM.

00:15.216 --> 00:18.489
I PAY THE BILLS THE SECOND
I SEE THEM IN THE MAIL.

00:18.489 --> 00:20.091
AND DO YOU REMEMBER
TWO MONTHS AGO,

00:20.091 --> 00:21.492
WHEN YOU GOT SAD
ABOUT TREES DYING

00:21.492 --> 00:23.494
AND PUT ALL OF OUR ACCOUNTS
ON PAPERLESS BILLING?

00:23.494 --> 00:24.725
DUH!

00:24.725 --> 00:27.298
NO PAPER BILLS,
LESS TREE MURDER.

00:28.499 --> 00:29.600
GIVE IT A SEC.
SHE'LL GET IT.

00:29.600 --> 00:31.662
OH, WAIT.

00:31.662 --> 00:35.035
PAPERLESS MEANS OUR BILLS
WON'T COME IN THE MAIL.

00:35.035 --> 00:38.339
AND IF OUR BILLS DON'T COME
IN THE MAIL, THEN...

00:38.339 --> 00:39.710
OH, CRAP!

00:39.710 --> 00:42.373
WELL, THEN WHAT?
WHAT HAPPENS?

00:42.373 --> 00:45.676
IT'S A MIRACLE I CAN EVEN TIE
MY OWN SHOES.

00:45.676 --> 00:47.678
в™Єв™Єв™Є

00:51.152 --> 00:52.623
OKAY, I FORGOT
TO PAY OUR BILLS.

00:52.623 --> 00:54.185
NOT A PROBLEM.

00:54.185 --> 00:56.227
IT'S OKAY. I'LL TAKE CARE
OF IT RIGHT NOW.

00:56.227 --> 00:58.629
I'LL TAKE CARE
OF IT LATER.

00:58.629 --> 01:00.431
OUR PHONE GOT SHUT OFF?!
JULES, DAMN IT!

01:00.431 --> 01:01.732
THAT IS SO IRRESPONSIBLE.

01:01.732 --> 01:03.594
I'M SO SORRY.
I KNOW THIS IS MY SCREW-UP.

01:03.594 --> 01:04.665
I'M GONNA FIX IT.

01:04.665 --> 01:06.467
DO IT SOON.
I'M FREEZING.

01:06.467 --> 01:09.300
THE PAPER SAID THE NEXT TWO DAYS
COULD HIT RECORD LOWS HERE.

01:09.300 --> 01:10.841
THERE'S A 10% CHANCE OF SNOW.

01:10.841 --> 01:12.703
SNOW?!

01:12.703 --> 01:14.405
AWESOME!

01:14.405 --> 01:16.677
MAN, WE CAN ALL BUILD SNOWMEN
AND WRITE OUR NAMES IN PEE!

01:16.677 --> 01:19.210
[ Sadly ] NOT EVERYONE CAN
WRITE THEIR NAME IN PEE.

01:19.210 --> 01:21.412
ARE YOU MORE UPSET ABOUT THAT
THAN SCREWING UP OUR BILLS?

01:21.412 --> 01:23.284
OF COURSE NOT.

01:23.284 --> 01:25.416
[ Voice breaking ]
WHO WOULD EVEN WANT TO...

01:25.416 --> 01:26.787
PEE THEIR NAME
IN THE SNOW?

01:30.861 --> 01:33.864
DID YOU KNOW THAT SOME PLACES
MAKE YOU PAY IN PERSON

01:33.864 --> 01:36.096
IF YOUR BILL IS LATE?
OF COURSE.

01:36.096 --> 01:37.498
WHEN I LIVED IN NEW YORK,

01:37.498 --> 01:39.300
I WOULD JUST WAIT UNTIL
I GOT THE THIRD LATE NOTICE.

01:39.300 --> 01:41.732
AND THEN I WOULD GO DOWN
TO THE BILLING OFFICE

01:41.732 --> 01:43.634
AND RUB UP AGAINST THE GUY
AT THE DESK.

01:43.634 --> 01:45.176
I NEVER HAD TO PAY.

01:45.176 --> 01:47.478
ALL RIGHT. I GOT TO GO DEAL
WITH THIS STUFF.

01:49.810 --> 01:52.613
YOU. YOU RAN OUT ON YOUR CHECK
AT BREAKFAST.

01:52.613 --> 01:54.385
YOU OWE ME 15 BUCKS.

01:54.385 --> 01:55.746
NO, I DON'T.

01:55.746 --> 01:57.518
MY BOYFRIEND SERVED ME
BREAKFAST IN BED,

01:57.518 --> 02:00.891
AND THEN I SERVED HIM
A LITTLE SIDE OF WHAT-WHAT?

02:00.891 --> 02:02.723
OH, NO.
DID SHE HAVE DARK HAIR?

02:02.723 --> 02:05.226
UGH! I BET IT WAS MISSY,
MY DOPPELGANGER.

02:05.226 --> 02:08.229
SHE LOOKS EXACTLY LIKE ME,
EXCEPT SHE NEVER HAS ANY MONEY.

02:08.229 --> 02:10.201
TELL HER.
YEAH, THAT'S NOT HAPPENING.

02:10.201 --> 02:11.502
I'M CALLING THE COPS.

02:11.502 --> 02:14.735
FINE! TAKE IT.

02:14.735 --> 02:16.707
YOU HAVE HEARD ALL
OF MY DOPPELGANGER STORIES!

02:16.707 --> 02:17.908
WHY DIDN'T YOU
BACK ME UP?!

02:17.908 --> 02:19.310
BECAUSE
YOU'RE SO FULL OF CRAP!

02:19.310 --> 02:20.811
YOU THINK I AM LYING?!

02:20.811 --> 02:23.544
ABSOLUTELY.
BUT IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

02:23.544 --> 02:25.145
I LIE ALL THE TIME.

02:25.145 --> 02:26.847
YOU THINK THAT ANDY
IS STAN'S FATHER?

02:26.847 --> 02:29.850
HE IS. I'M JOKING.

02:29.850 --> 02:31.652
WHAT?

02:31.652 --> 02:35.356
YEAH, I'M TRYING TO FIND OUT HOW
MUCH I OWE ON MY CAR INSURANCE.

02:35.356 --> 02:37.288
[ HORNS HONK ]

02:37.288 --> 02:39.530
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN, "LAPSED"?

02:39.530 --> 02:41.892
OH, STUPID RING.

02:41.892 --> 02:43.264
[ LOUD CRASH ]

02:43.264 --> 02:45.596
[ SIGHS ]

02:45.596 --> 02:47.698
OH. THAT'S WHAT THAT MEANS.

02:48.839 --> 02:50.501
SHOO! WHOO!

02:50.501 --> 02:52.503
[ LAUGHS ]
CHECK OUT MY DUDS!

02:52.503 --> 02:55.546
YOU LOOK LIKE THE HERO
OF EVERY '80s SKI MOVIE!

02:55.546 --> 02:56.807
"THE ONLY WAY
OFF THIS MOUNTAIN

02:56.807 --> 02:58.709
IS DOWN
THE DEVIL'S CHUTE."

02:58.709 --> 03:00.781
[ LAUGHS ]
WHAT DOES "BEST" MEAN?

03:00.781 --> 03:02.913
I MADE ONE FOR YOU, TOO.

03:02.913 --> 03:05.185
[ GASPS ]
NO! I LOVE IT!

03:05.185 --> 03:07.588
Travis: YOU KNOW,
THE WEATHER REPORT

03:07.588 --> 03:09.590
SAID THERE WAS ONLY
A 10% CHANCE.

03:09.590 --> 03:11.362
FOR SNOW!

03:11.362 --> 03:12.593
I'VE ALWAYS WANTED TO WAKE UP
TO A WINTER WONDERLAND,

03:12.593 --> 03:14.395
AND IT'S FINALLY GONNA HAPPEN!

03:14.395 --> 03:17.698
HERE. I GOT THIS FOR YOU FOR OUR
FIRST FATHER-SON SNOWBALL FIGHT.

03:17.698 --> 03:18.899
AAH!
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:18.899 --> 03:20.301
ALL RIGHT.

03:20.301 --> 03:22.573
I'M OFF TO STOCK UP
ON CANNED GOODS!

03:22.573 --> 03:24.335
SHOO!

03:24.335 --> 03:26.777
YOU THINK HE'S A LITTLE
OVERLY EXCITED FOR SOMETHING

03:26.777 --> 03:28.609
THAT ALMOST DEFINITELY
ISN'T HAPPENING?

03:28.609 --> 03:31.482
I GOT SNOW IN MY EAR!
IT'S SO COLD!

03:31.482 --> 03:32.913
HEY, BABE.
HI.

03:32.913 --> 03:34.915
HOW'S YOUR DAY?
NOT BAD.

03:34.915 --> 03:36.787
AND I REALLY MEANT THAT.

03:36.787 --> 03:40.251
THOSE WEREN'T JUST WORDS THAT
I'M SAYING THAT ARE NOT TRUE.

03:40.251 --> 03:41.622
WOULD YOU MOVE ON?

03:41.622 --> 03:43.924
ALL I DID WAS CALL YOU
A HUGE LIAR.

03:43.924 --> 03:45.326
OH, BOY.

03:45.326 --> 03:46.627
I DO NOT LIE!

03:46.627 --> 03:49.760
LYING IS FOR PEOPLE
THAT HIDE THINGS.

03:49.760 --> 03:51.332
I HIDE NOTHING.

03:51.332 --> 03:52.833
I LEARNED THAT THE HARD WAY

03:52.833 --> 03:54.505
WHEN I DROPPED MY NAPKIN
UNDER THE TABLE LAST WEEK.

03:54.505 --> 03:57.438
SO, THERE'S NO FICTION
OR EXAGGERATION

03:57.438 --> 03:59.540
IN YOUR TALES
OF WORLD TRAVEL

03:59.540 --> 04:01.672
OR PSEUDO-CELEBRITY
SEXUAL ENCOUNTERS

04:01.672 --> 04:03.974
OR FRIENDS WHO GIVE BIRTH
ON DANCE FLOORS?

04:03.974 --> 04:07.548
I HAD ONE FRIEND WHO DROPPED
FETUS ON A DANCE FLOOR.

04:07.548 --> 04:08.949
NO SANE PERSON COULD BELIEVE

04:08.949 --> 04:10.881
THE NONSENSE
THAT YOU SAY IS TRUE.

04:10.881 --> 04:12.823
WELL,
I ALWAYS BELIEVED HER.

04:12.823 --> 04:14.685
YOU DON'T COUNT.
SHE LETS YOU SEE HER NAKED.

04:14.685 --> 04:15.856
KNUCKLEHEADS?

04:15.856 --> 04:17.458
NEVER THOUGHT
SHE WAS LYING.

04:17.458 --> 04:19.290
ME, NEITHER.

04:19.290 --> 04:21.332
WELL, I THEN I HAVE BAD NEWS
FOR YOU -- YOU'RE ALL IDIOTS.

04:21.332 --> 04:22.793
AND IT WILL BE UP TO ME

04:22.793 --> 04:24.495
TO PROVE THAT OUR FRIEND J.B.
IS FULL OF B.S.

04:24.495 --> 04:25.536
Laurie: DO YOUR WORST.

04:25.536 --> 04:27.037
MY RAP IS BULLETPROOF.

04:27.037 --> 04:29.670
NOT UNLIKE
MY FOSTER BROTHER, ZIG,

04:29.670 --> 04:32.943
WHO, AFTER A SERIOUS
LION-TAMING MISHAP,

04:32.943 --> 04:35.676
HAD TO BE COMPLETELY REBUILT
USING A COMPLICATED...

04:36.877 --> 04:40.311
OH, BOY.
GRAYSON'S GONNA FREAK!

04:41.852 --> 04:45.055
ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR MIND?!

04:45.055 --> 04:47.658
I'M SORRY. I DIDN'T REALIZE
HOW ATTRACTIVE YOU ARE.

04:47.658 --> 04:50.391
WOULD YOU MIND IF I ASKED YOU
THAT QUESTION WITHOUT YELLING?

04:50.391 --> 04:51.722
OKAY.

04:51.722 --> 04:53.394
ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR MIND?

04:53.394 --> 04:55.866
I'M SO SORRY.

04:55.866 --> 04:57.868
THIS CAR'S REALLY EXPENSIVE,
ISN'T IT?

04:57.868 --> 05:00.731
WELL, IT WAS UNTIL A COUPLE
OF MINUTES AGO.

05:00.731 --> 05:02.903
I HAVE
THIS INSURANCE ISSUE.

05:02.903 --> 05:04.835
WHY DON'T WE FORGET
ABOUT THIS WHOLE THING

05:04.835 --> 05:06.837
AND GRAB A CUP OF COFFEE,
TAKE A DEEP BREATH,

05:06.837 --> 05:08.579
AND I CAN TRY TO FIGURE OUT

05:08.579 --> 05:11.011
HOW SOMEONE AS INCREDIBLE
AS YOU ARE ISN'T MARRIED.

05:11.011 --> 05:13.544
[ CHUCKLES ]
WELL, ACTUALLY, I...

05:14.915 --> 05:16.787
I'M JULES.

05:16.787 --> 05:19.450
I'M SAM.
SHALL WE?

05:19.450 --> 05:21.091
SURE.

05:23.424 --> 05:24.625
ELLIE!

05:24.625 --> 05:25.996
I LOST MY INSURANCE,
I REAR-ENDED A GUY,

05:25.996 --> 05:27.658
AND NOW I'M ON A FAKE DATE
TO TRY TO GET OUT OF IT

05:27.658 --> 05:29.530
SO GRAYSON DOESN'T KILL ME.
HOW DO I FLIRT?

05:29.530 --> 05:31.061
BAT YOUR EYES,
FLIP YOUR HAIR,

05:31.061 --> 05:34.805
LAUGH AT EVERYTHING HE SAYS,
AND ROCK THAT CLEAVAGE.

05:34.805 --> 05:36.066
THANKS, BYE.

05:36.066 --> 05:38.469
ALL RIGHT, BAT...

05:40.811 --> 05:43.043
OH.

05:43.043 --> 05:45.516
YOU DIDN'T INJURE THOSE
DURING THE CRASH, DID YOU?

05:45.516 --> 05:46.747
OH, NO.
UH, THEY'RE FINE.

05:46.747 --> 05:48.479
I WAS JUST DOUBLE-CHECKING,
YOU KNOW.

05:48.479 --> 05:50.921
[ CHUCKLES ]
"HONK-HONK. AH-OOGAH!"

05:50.921 --> 05:52.823
[ LAUGHS ]
THEY'RE GOOD.

05:52.823 --> 05:54.585
WELL, THAT'S A RELIEF.

05:54.585 --> 05:56.987
IT'S HARD TO FIND A REPLACEMENT
HORN FROM THE 1930s.

05:56.987 --> 06:00.360
[ LAUGHS LOUDLY ]

06:01.562 --> 06:03.794
SO, UM, YOU DON'T LIVE HERE
IN TOWN?

06:03.794 --> 06:06.467
NO, I'M JUST HERE
ON MY WAY THROUGH MIAMI.

06:06.467 --> 06:08.999
MY VENTURE CAPITAL FIRM
IS INVESTING IN --

06:08.999 --> 06:12.643
THIS IS REALLY BORING.
TELL ME ABOUT YOU.

06:12.643 --> 06:13.674
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

06:13.674 --> 06:14.745
WELL, I LIKE WINE.

06:14.745 --> 06:17.808
OKAY.

06:17.808 --> 06:19.980
OH, AND I ALSO
SELL REAL ESTATE.

06:19.980 --> 06:22.483
I LIKE THAT
YOU STARTED WITH WINE.

06:22.483 --> 06:24.555
I LIKE A NICE CHIANTI,
AND NOT JUST BECAUSE

06:24.555 --> 06:26.487
THAT'S WHAT HANNIBAL LECTER
WOULD DRINK

06:26.487 --> 06:28.158
WHEN HE ATE PEOPLE.
HANNIBAL WHO?

06:28.158 --> 06:31.061
LECTER, FROM THE MOVIE
"SILENCE OF THE LAMBS."

06:31.061 --> 06:33.664
THERE WERE SILENT LAMBS?
WELL, NO, NOT REALLY.

06:33.664 --> 06:34.965
THEY WERE MORE OF A SYMBOL.

06:34.965 --> 06:37.027
[ LAUGHS ]

06:38.929 --> 06:40.070
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

06:40.070 --> 06:41.772
SO YOU OWN
YOUR OWN BUSINESS?

06:41.772 --> 06:43.173
HOW DID THAT HAPPEN?

06:43.173 --> 06:45.776
OH, OKAY.
WELL, A FEW YEARS AGO,

06:45.776 --> 06:47.608
I WAS IN A BAD
MOUNTAIN-CLIMBING ACCIDENT.

06:47.608 --> 06:48.839
[ GASPS ]
OH, NO.

06:48.839 --> 06:50.040
DON'T WORRY,
I DIDN'T DIE OR ANYTHING.

06:50.040 --> 06:51.181
OH.

06:51.181 --> 06:52.743
BUT IT WAS
A REALLY BAD FALL,

06:52.743 --> 06:54.845
AND IT MADE ME REALIZE
THAT LIFE IS A GIFT

06:54.845 --> 06:56.647
AND WE HAVE TO MAKE THE MOST
OF EVERY DAY.

06:56.647 --> 06:58.549
SO, I BOUGHT MY OWN COMPANY,

06:58.549 --> 07:00.921
I MADE AN UNGODLY
AMOUNT OF MONEY,

07:00.921 --> 07:02.623
AND NOW I JUST SPEND
MY WHOLE LIFE

07:02.623 --> 07:04.124
JUST TRAVELING
AND ENJOYING MYSELF.

07:04.124 --> 07:05.756
FALLING OFF THAT MOUNTAIN

07:05.756 --> 07:07.197
WAS THE BEST THING
THAT EVER HAPPENED TO ME.

07:07.197 --> 07:09.860
I FELL OFF
THIS REALLY TALL CHAIR ONCE.

07:09.860 --> 07:11.532
AND WHEN I HIT THE FLOOR,

07:11.532 --> 07:14.735
I FOUND MY MISSING HAIRBRUSH
RIGHT THERE UNDER THE COUCH.

07:14.735 --> 07:15.836
OH.

07:15.836 --> 07:17.568
YOUR STORY'S BETTER.

07:17.568 --> 07:18.639
WAS IT A GOOD BRUSH?

07:18.639 --> 07:20.010
IT WAS A GREAT BRUSH.

07:20.010 --> 07:21.211
THEN I'D CALL IT A TIE.

07:23.173 --> 07:26.677
[ LAUGHS ]

07:29.680 --> 07:33.153
HO. LEE. MAJORS.

07:33.153 --> 07:35.956
I HAVE SPENT
THE LAST FEW HOURS

07:35.956 --> 07:39.490
MAPPING OUT EVERY STORY
YOU'VE EVER TOLD.

07:39.490 --> 07:41.231
WHICH HAS BEEN GREAT
FOR BUSINESS.

07:41.231 --> 07:44.895
SO, IF YOU DON'T MIND, I'D LIKE
TO CONFIRM A FEW DETAILS.

07:44.895 --> 07:48.569
SO, YOU WERE BORN
AND CONCEIVED IN A JACUZZI.

07:48.569 --> 07:51.742
YEAH.
YOUR MOM WAS
A WHITESNAKE GROUPIE,

07:51.742 --> 07:54.244
AND YOUR DAD WAS A POLITICIAN
WHO KNOCKED HER UP

07:54.244 --> 07:57.047
AND THEN LEFT TO BE WITH
HIS OWN LEGITIMATE FAMILY.

07:57.047 --> 08:00.150
YEAH.
YOU'VE HAD FIVE STEPDADS,
COUNTLESS FOSTER DADS,

08:00.150 --> 08:04.655
AND YOU HAVE BEEN
MEDICALLY DEAD...FOUR TIMES?

08:04.655 --> 08:06.186
BEACH, RAVE,
RODEO, KID ROCK SHOW.

08:06.186 --> 08:07.718
THAT'S FOUR.

08:07.718 --> 08:11.191
YOU'VE BEEN MOLESTED [SIGHS]
BY A DOLPHIN...

08:11.191 --> 08:14.494
UGH.
...ATTACKED
BY AN ANIMATRONIC BEAR,

08:14.494 --> 08:16.997
EAR RIPPED OFF BY A FALCON,

08:16.997 --> 08:19.199
AND ROBIN WILLIAMS
SLEPT WITH YOUR NIECE.

08:19.199 --> 08:21.632
REMEMBER, HER FOOT GOT CAUGHT
IN HIS ARM HAIR.

08:21.632 --> 08:23.734
THEY HAD TO CALL THE PARAMEDICS
TO GET HER OUT.

08:23.734 --> 08:25.105
YOU GO TO A PSYCHIC

08:25.105 --> 08:27.738
WHOSE HANDS WERE RIPPED OFF
BY A CHIMP,

08:27.738 --> 08:30.510
AND YOU HAVE A FRIEND
WITH ROBOT ARMS.

08:30.510 --> 08:32.543
AWW! AMANDA!

08:32.543 --> 08:34.715
AND ANOTHER
WITH ROBOT LEGS.

08:34.715 --> 08:36.617
UGH. NEZZIE.

08:36.617 --> 08:42.753
NOW THAT WE ARE CLEAR
ON THE INSANE DETAILS...

08:42.753 --> 08:49.159
I AM GONNA FIND THE HOLE
THAT SINKS THIS SHIP OF LIES.

08:50.961 --> 08:53.704
[ SIGHS ]

08:53.704 --> 08:55.005
Andy: [ CHUCKLES ]

08:55.005 --> 08:56.937
SOMEONE'S GETTING
AN EPIC SPANKING!

08:56.937 --> 08:59.139
AAH!
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

08:59.139 --> 09:01.672
I GOT THIS FROM MY BUDDY RON
AT THE PIZZA PALACE.

09:01.672 --> 09:04.044
CAN YOU BELIEVE I COULDN'T FIND
A SNOW SHOVEL ANYWHERE IN TOWN?

09:04.044 --> 09:06.617
YES.
BECAUSE THIS IS FLORIDA.

09:06.617 --> 09:08.248
WHERE IT NEVER SNOWS.

09:08.248 --> 09:09.820
UNTIL NOW.

09:09.820 --> 09:12.222
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

09:12.222 --> 09:14.625
HELP ME OUT.

09:14.625 --> 09:16.627
OW! FINE.
[ SIGHS ]

09:16.627 --> 09:20.831
BOBBY, YOU KNOW I GET EXCITED
WHEN YOU GET EXCITED,

09:20.831 --> 09:24.294
BUT THE NEWS REPORT
DID SAY "10% CHANCE."

09:24.294 --> 09:25.866
RIGHT.

09:25.866 --> 09:27.137
FOR SNOW!

09:27.137 --> 09:28.198
YEAH! SNOW!

09:28.198 --> 09:29.870
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

09:29.870 --> 09:31.101
IT'S GONNA SNOW, BABY!

09:31.101 --> 09:32.903
OHH.
SORRY, I TRIED.

09:32.903 --> 09:34.274
DID YOU? DAD, I FEEL LIKE

09:34.274 --> 09:35.906
YOU'RE ONLY HEARING
WHAT YOU WANT TO HEAR.

09:35.906 --> 09:37.147
LOOK, I JUST DON'T WANT YOU
TO BE DISAPPOINTED

09:37.147 --> 09:38.609
WHEN IT DOESN'T SNOW.

09:38.609 --> 09:41.111
POWER OF POSITIVE
THINKING, TRAV.

09:41.111 --> 09:44.985
WHEN I BELIEVE SOMETHING'S
GONNA HAPPEN, IT DOES.

09:44.985 --> 09:47.017
WINE ME.

09:47.017 --> 09:50.020
MY HEAD IS SWIMMING
WITH LAURIE KELLER TALES

09:50.020 --> 09:51.221
OF SMUT AND LIES.

09:51.221 --> 09:53.994
OH, HOW DID YOUR DATE GO?

09:53.994 --> 09:55.265
AMAZING!

09:55.265 --> 09:57.197
I LAUGHED, I FLIPPED MY HAIR,

09:57.197 --> 09:59.870
I GAVE HIM AN EYEFUL
OF BIG LEFTY AND SHORTSTACK.

09:59.870 --> 10:01.131
HE DIDN'T KNOW WHAT HIT HIM.

10:01.131 --> 10:02.272
WHAT?

10:02.272 --> 10:04.334
OH, RIGHT.
I DIDN'T TELL YOU.

10:04.334 --> 10:07.077
YOU SEE, I HIT
THIS REALLY EXPENSIVE CAR

10:07.077 --> 10:09.710
RIGHT AFTER I FOUND OUT THAT
OUR CAR INSURANCE HAD LAPSED.

10:09.710 --> 10:11.882
LAPSED?
IT MEANS EXPIRED.

10:11.882 --> 10:13.613
READ A BOOK SOMETIME.

10:13.613 --> 10:15.085
MY RING FELL OFF,

10:15.085 --> 10:16.847
AND THE DRIVER OF THE CAR
ASKED ME FOR COFFEE.

10:16.847 --> 10:18.388
AND THEN I GOT SOME
FLIRTING TIPS FROM ELLIE,

10:18.388 --> 10:20.090
AND THEN HE SAID,
"FORGET THE WHOLE THING."

10:20.090 --> 10:21.221
PLEASE DON'T BE MAD.

10:21.221 --> 10:24.294
[ Chuckling ]
THAT IS AWESOME!

10:24.294 --> 10:26.196
SO, I DID GOOD?

10:26.196 --> 10:29.359
YOU DID SO GOOD I'M A LITTLE
TURNED ON RIGHT NOW.

10:29.359 --> 10:31.662
OOH.
COME HERE.

10:31.662 --> 10:33.163
[ CHUCKLES ]
MMM.
MMM.

10:33.163 --> 10:34.364
OHH.

10:34.364 --> 10:36.667
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:36.667 --> 10:38.769
YOU DON'T HAVE TO STAY
AND WATCH.

10:38.769 --> 10:39.940
I KNOW.

10:39.940 --> 10:42.943
OH, OKAY.
MMM.

10:46.646 --> 10:48.318
HOW LONG'S
SHE BEEN AT THIS?

10:48.318 --> 10:49.750
HOURS.

10:49.750 --> 10:51.321
SHE'S ON HER EIGHTH CUP
OF COFFEE

10:51.321 --> 10:52.422
AND HASN'T LEFT TO PEE.

10:52.422 --> 10:54.354
SHE CAN STARE
TILL SHE'S DEAD,

10:54.354 --> 10:56.286
'CAUSE ALL MY DEETS
CHECK OUT.

10:56.286 --> 10:58.929
BELIZE! HO-HO!

10:58.929 --> 11:04.094
YOU SAID THAT YOU WENT
ON A CRUISE TO BELIZE

11:04.094 --> 11:07.067
AND YOU BROKE UP A FIGHT
BETWEEN RIVAL DRUG GANGS

11:07.067 --> 11:10.300
BY TURNING YOUR BODY
INTO A HUMAN ICE LUGE.

11:10.300 --> 11:13.704
AND?
YOU'VE NEVER BEEN TO BELIZE.

11:13.704 --> 11:17.447
[ SCOFFS ]
YEAH, I HAVE.

11:17.447 --> 11:19.109
WE WENT THERE
RIGHT AFTER --

11:19.109 --> 11:21.251
OKAY. WELL...

11:21.251 --> 11:23.283
YOU KNOW,
MAYBE IT WAS PARAGUAY.

11:23.283 --> 11:26.156
THERE IT IS,
THE HOLE IN THIS SHIP!

11:26.156 --> 11:29.760
AND WITH THAT ONE LIE, THAT
CALLS EVERYTHING INTO QUESTION.

11:29.760 --> 11:31.091
RULING?

11:31.091 --> 11:33.794
TECHNICALLY SPEAKING,
I HAVE TO AGREE.

11:33.794 --> 11:35.926
SORRY, LAURIE.

11:35.926 --> 11:37.898
OH. HERE COMES MY DAD.

11:37.898 --> 11:40.330
HOPE HE'S NOT TOO CRUSHED
IT DIDN'T SNOW LAST NIGHT.

11:40.330 --> 11:43.373
WHAT'S UP, GUYS?
YOU'RE OKAY!

11:43.373 --> 11:45.736
I'M BETTER THAN OKAY.
MAN, I'M GREAT!

11:45.736 --> 11:47.908
SO, YOU'RE NOT UPSET
THAT IT DIDN'T SNOW?

11:47.908 --> 11:50.781
THE NEWS SAID IT WAS GONNA SNOW
TODAY OR TOMORROW,

11:50.781 --> 11:53.383
WHICH MEANS IT'S DEFINITELY
GONNA SNOW TOMORROW!

11:53.383 --> 11:57.187
A 10% CHANCE HAS NOW BEEN
CUT IN HALF --

11:57.187 --> 11:58.849
A 100% CHANCE!

11:58.849 --> 12:00.791
ALL RIGHT. I'M GONNA GO
FILL THIS UP WITH WHISKEY

12:00.791 --> 12:02.452
IN CASE DOG TRAVIS HAS TO GO
MAKE SOME RESCUES

12:02.452 --> 12:05.495
OR IF HE MEETS A CUTE BITCH
AND WANTS TO GET FUNKY.

12:05.495 --> 12:06.957
[ LAUGHS ]

12:08.799 --> 12:10.130
[ GASPS ]

12:10.130 --> 12:11.401
HI, BABE.

12:11.401 --> 12:13.103
WHY DON'T YOU GRAB US
SOME COFFEE?

12:13.103 --> 12:14.364
OKAY. YOU WANT, LIKE, A REGULAR
COFFEE, OR LIKE A FRAPPU--

12:14.364 --> 12:16.436
SOUNDS GREAT!
ALL RIGHT!

12:16.436 --> 12:18.008
HI.
HEY.

12:18.008 --> 12:21.111
I SAW YOUR PICTURE ON ONE
OF YOUR BUS BENCH ADS,

12:21.111 --> 12:23.914
AND I FIGURED THIS IS
PROBABLY WHERE YOU WORK.

12:23.914 --> 12:25.916
I'VE BEEN SITTING HERE
FOR ABOUT FOUR HOURS.

12:25.916 --> 12:27.377
YOU DON'T WORK VERY MUCH,
DO YOU?

12:27.377 --> 12:29.049
WHICH AD WAS IT?

12:29.049 --> 12:31.351
DID IT HAVE MUSTACHE GRAFFITI
OR PENIS GRAFFITI?

12:31.351 --> 12:35.385
NO, THIS ONE WAS PENIS
WITH A MUSTACHE ON IT.

12:35.385 --> 12:37.287
OH, THAT'S MY FAVORITE!
MINE, TOO, ODDLY.

12:37.287 --> 12:38.358
[ LAUGHS ]

12:38.358 --> 12:39.930
HEY,
YOU REMEMBER WHAT I SAID

12:39.930 --> 12:41.431
ABOUT LIVING LIFE
TO THE FULLEST,

12:41.431 --> 12:43.063
MAKING THE MOST
OF EVERY DAY?

12:43.063 --> 12:44.234
YEAH.

12:44.234 --> 12:47.838
5, 6, 7, 8!

12:47.838 --> 12:50.200
